commit.message:
Correct connection failure tests

* use a bad port instead of a bad host as
  we now use inet to check the host we
  give
revert to the backwards compatible behaviour when no_reconnect option is passed

Unix domain socket support.

Requires OTP 19+.

Issue #83

This commit moves initial connection process out of init to avoid
blocking or crashing supervisor. Besides if reconnect is allowed
it will be used even if connection failed right after init.
Travis-CI no longer supports IPv6 on newer build enviroments.
